{
  "texts": [
    "However, following various prompts, it was observed that ChatGPT 4 could answer the question correctly, while ChatCPT 3.5 could not.",
    "These findings do not fully align with those of Wardat et al. (2023).",
    "According to another finding of the study, it was found that both versions made mistakes especially in probability questions.",
    "In addition, it was observed that ChatGPT 4 applied the basic rule of the angle-edge relation in the angle question in a national mathematics exam but did not pay attention to the detail that one of the two angles given is greater than the other.",
    "Here, it is understood that ChatGPT 4 knew the basic rule of the angle-edge relation but could not establish the angle-edge relation when another variable related to the angle was given."
  ]
}